Comment: What can I say? I am a fan of my Indian systems.
What can I say? I am a fan of my Indian systems.
I particularly like the Nimzo-Indian Defense for Black. I have spent time studying over-the-board games for many years and Indian systems make for a more dynamic game for both sides.

! - a solid response. This attacks the f-line pawn and the weakened h6 pawn. I considered several options here: 1) defending with the queen - Qf8, preventing further attacks on that line, but I think I lose tempo 2) g5?? - while this option may look appealing, after 24) ... g5 25) Bxg5! hxg5 26) Qxg5+! Kf8 27) Rh3 f6 28) Qg4 ... I'm not really liking this for black. The kingside is completely destroyed, which leaves me with a losing position. This leads to another option which I eventually chose...
